Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 12:47:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Rework exam/feedback/enrollment flow + dedupe Module 9

Implements the 5 requested fixes:

1. Pre-test now locked until all 9 modules complete, then auto-unlocks
   (was always-open). Gated in hub_student and forms portal.
2. Removed the shock fluid-bolus row from the Module 9 pharmacology table
   (it duplicates Module 4); replaced with Ketamine (RSI induction).
3. Registration now captures/confirms the registrant's full name so
   admin-by-email invites still produce a real profile name.
4. Final exam is hidden from students entirely until an admin/instructor
   unlocks it (global flag or per-student examUnlocked); removed the old
   auto-unlock-at-9-modules behaviour.
5. Course feedback is now student-facing and gates the exam: one record per
   student (students/{uid}.feedback), required before the exam, editable
   until the exam is unlocked, then frozen. Submitting once is still allowed
   if the exam was unlocked before any feedback existed (no deadlock).

Supporting:
- firebase-sync.js: add FB.saveFeedback(); loadAndSync() returns feedback +
  examUnlocked.
- hub_instructor.html: roster feedback chip; richer roster CSV export.
- No firestore.rules change needed (feedback uses existing students write).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
